# DNS Resolution

## DNS Flow

User enters

www.google.com

↓

Computer checks local DNS cache

↓

Queries configured DNS server

↓

Receives IP address

↓

Connects to destination

---

## Commands Practiced

Check configured DNS

```bash
cat /etc/resolv.conf
```

---

DNS lookup

```bash
nslookup google.com
```

---

Verify hostname resolution

```bash
ping google.com
```

---

# DNS Troubleshooting Workflow

Problem

User cannot open websites

↓

Check IP Address

```bash
ip addr
```

↓

Check Default Gateway

```bash
ip route
```

↓

Ping Gateway

↓

Ping Public IP

```bash
ping 8.8.8.8
```

↓

Ping Hostname

```bash
ping google.com
```

↓

If IP works but hostname fails

↓

Suspect DNS

↓

Check

```bash
cat /etc/resolv.conf
```

↓

Verify DNS service

↓

Update DNS configuration (according to company policy)

↓

Verify issue resolved

